<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,439,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,726,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is separated from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter" authorityYear="1988" box="[885,1033,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neometrypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[885,1033,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Neometrypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: general coloration brownish orange, abdominal tergites crossed lengthwise by median and lateral bands dark brown. Male: median projection of metanotum triangular, burnt red. Male genitalia: anterior margin of pseudepiphallic sclerite sub-straight on median region; LLophi straight, inclined inwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,439,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,870,896]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,591,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">General morphology.</emphasis>
Head. Fastigium as long as wide, pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1188,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Lateral ocelli rounded, median ocellus absent (
<figureCitation box="[459,549,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); frons smooth (
<figureCitation box="[736,826,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Antennal scape longer than wide, inner margin with bristles. Maxillary palpi articles 4 and 5 almost same-sized, article 3 slightly longer; article 5 slightly upcurved (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" startId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" targetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1665,1725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1665,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Campos &amp; Souza-Dias, 2021" authorityName="Campos &amp; Souza-Dias" authorityYear="2021" box="[287,519,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neometrypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azevedoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[287,519,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Neometrypus azevedoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,587,1665,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[527,587,1665,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1771,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
Thorax. DD as long as wide, covered by bristles. DD cephalic margin sub-straight, caudal margin straight (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). LL ventro-cephalic angle rounded; ventro-caudal angle gradually ascendant in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1360,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). FWs surpassing posterior margin of metanotum (
<figureCitation box="[640,730,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1771,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Legs. TI with three apical spurs, two ventral, one dorsal. TII with three apical spurs, two ventral, one dorsal. TIII subapical spurs have two (sometimes one) spines between each spur, five or seven spines above subapical spurs on inner and outer sides. TIII inner apical spurs: iad&gt;iam&gt;iav; outer apical spurs: oam&gt;oav&gt;oad. Basitarsus dorsal spines 2/1 sometimes 2/2; outer and inner apical spurs same-sized.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,1244,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
Abdomen. Tergites pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[547,637,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); Supra anal plate posterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1231,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis box="[199,264,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Male.</emphasis>
Median projection of metanotum triangular; anterior margin slightly rounded, posterior margin wider than anterior margin in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[567,658,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate longer than wide, posterior margin almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis box="[199,365,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[381,507,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4A–D</figureCitation>
). Pseudepiphallus: pseudepiphallic sclerite almost straight in lateral view; anterior margin sub-straight on median region, lateral region upcurved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1134,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). LLophi straight, inclined inwards, posterior margin rounded in dorsal and ventral views; inner margin membranous, outer margin sclerotized, thin (
<figureCitation box="[211,336,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
). PsP almost same-sized as LLophi, posterior margin divided into two lobes, not surpassing posterior margin of pseudepiphallic sclerite in dorsal and ventral views (
<figureCitation box="[937,1027,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); apex of dorsal lobe finger-shaped, inclined inwards; apex of ventral lobe truncated. r elongate, longer than pseudepiphallic sclerite, flattened laterally (
<figureCitation box="[160,284,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). Ectophallic invagination: EctAp longer than LLophi, straight, slightly inclined to outwards in dorsal and ventral views (
<figureCitation box="[369,462,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,679,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-202@6.[151,1436,669,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male genitalia: A—dorsal, B—ventral, C—lateral, D—posterior. Scale 1mm. Abbreviations see material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); arc not complete, curved posteriorly; ventral projections of ectophallic invagination shorter than arc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,415,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis box="[199,291,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
