<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,344,658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis box="[199,330,344,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Coloration.</emphasis>
Occiput, vertex, pronotum, and abdominal tergites brownish orange (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1217,344,370]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Occiput with two median longitudinal reddish stripes (
<figureCitation box="[562,652,380,406]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); face yellowish-brown with stripes gray on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1422,380,406]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); antennal scape and antennomeres yellowish-brown. FWs slightly translucent, orange; median projection of metanotum burnt red, apex whitish (
<figureCitation box="[509,600,452,478]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites crossed lengthwise by median and lateral bands dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[240,333,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); sternites dark brown, anterior and posterior margins light brown; supra anal plate dark brown, posterior margin grayish (
<figureCitation box="[440,526,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[872,956,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); cerci light brown. FI and FII light brown, medium brown spotted, TI and TII light brown; FIII yellowish-brown to light brown, slightly striped, distal apex reddish-brown; TIII dark brown, proximal portion reddish-brown; spurs light brown with apex and basis medium brown; tarsomeres light brown (
<figureCitation box="[511,599,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1036,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-259@5.[151,1435,1029,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neometrypus azevedoi n. sp. Male: A—habitus, dorsal; B—habitus, lateral, C—head, frontal; D—metanotum, dorsal; E—supra anal plate; F—subgenital plate and last abdominal sternites. Scales A–B: 5mm, C–F: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5637884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5637884/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
